## Comprehensive Exploration Report: apps/web/src

I've completed a thorough exploration of the web application's directory structure, component patterns, and styling architecture. Here's what I found:

### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE (All Files in apps/web/src)

The project is organized as follows:

**Root Level Files (Core Setup):**
- `main.tsx` - React DOM entry point with router initialization
- `index.css` - Global styles with Tailwind CSS
- `router.ts` - TanStack Router configuration
- `env.ts` - Environment detection (Electron vs Browser)
- `branding.ts` - Branding constants
- `types.ts` - TypeScript type definitions

**Stores & State Management:**
- `store.ts` - Zustand store for app state (projects, threads)
- `composerDraftStore.ts` - Zustand store for composer drafts with persistence
- `terminalStateStore.ts` - Zustand store for terminal state
- `appSettings.ts` - App settings management
- `pendingUserInput.ts` - Pending user input state

**Routes Directory** (`routes/`):
- `__root.tsx` - Root layout with providers and error handling
- `_chat.tsx` - Chat layout with sidebar
- `_chat.index.tsx` - Chat index page
- `_chat.$threadId.tsx` - Individual thread view
- `_chat.settings.tsx` - Settings page

**Components Directory** (`components/`):
- **Main Components:**
  - `Sidebar.tsx` - Project/thread sidebar (15.6KB)
  - `ChatView.tsx` - Chat message display
  - `ThreadTerminalDrawer.tsx` - Terminal output drawer
  - `DiffPanel.tsx` - Diff viewer
  - `PlanSidebar.tsx` - Plan sidebar
  - `ComposerPromptEditor.tsx` - Message composer
  - `BranchToolbar.tsx` - Git branch controls
  - `GitActionsControl.tsx` - Git operations UI
  - `ProjectScriptsControl.tsx` - Project script management
  - `Icons.tsx` - Icon collection

- **UI Components** (`components/ui/`):
  - Base primitives from shadcn/ui adapted for Base UI React
  - `button.tsx` - Button with CVA variants
  - `card.tsx` - Card components with frame variants
  - `sidebar.tsx` - Sidebar layout primitives
  - `toast.tsx` - Toast notifications
  - `input.tsx`, `label.tsx`, `form.tsx` - Form elements
  - `dialog.tsx`, `popover.tsx`, `sheet.tsx` - Dialogs
  - `scroll-area.tsx`, `textarea.tsx` - Other controls
  - Many more: checkbox, radio-group, select, toggle, combobox, autocomplete, etc.

**Hooks Directory** (`hooks/`):
- `useTheme.ts` - Theme management (light/dark/system)
- `useMediaQuery.ts` - Media query hook
- `useTurnDiffSummaries.ts` - Diff summaries hook

**Library Directory** (`lib/`):
- `utils.ts` - Utility functions (cn, classname merging)
- `gitReactQuery.ts` - Git-related React Query options
- `projectReactQuery.ts` - Project-related queries
- `providerReactQuery.ts` - Provider-related queries
- `serverReactQuery.ts` - Server-related queries
- `diffRendering.ts` - Diff rendering logic
- `turnDiffTree.ts` - Diff tree utilities
- `terminalStateCleanup.ts` - Terminal cleanup logic
- `lruCache.ts` - LRU cache implementation
- `projectScriptKeybindings.ts` - Keybinding logic

**Utilities & Logic:**
- `keybindings.ts` - Keybinding management
- `terminal-links.ts` - Terminal link extraction
- `markdown-links.ts` - Markdown link handling
- `composer-logic.ts` - Composer state logic
- `composer-editor-mentions.ts` - Mention suggestions
- `session-logic.ts` - Session management logic
- `proposedPlan.ts` - Plan proposal utilities
- `nativeApi.ts` - Native API access
- `wsNativeApi.ts` - WebSocket native API
- `wsTransport.ts` - WebSocket transport
- `terminalActivity.ts` - Terminal activity tracking
- `terminalStateStore.ts` - Terminal state management
- `worktreeCleanup.ts` - Worktree cleanup utilities
- `truncateTitle.ts` - Title truncation
- `vscode-icons.ts` - VSCode icon support
- `projectScripts.ts` - Project scripts management
- `diffRouteSearch.ts` - Diff route searching
- `historyBootstrap.ts` - History initialization
- `chat-scroll.ts` - Chat scroll behavior
- `contextMenuFallback.ts` - Context menu handling
- `desktopUpdate.logic.ts` - Desktop update logic

### 2. MAIN APP COMPONENT (App.tsx via Router)

The application uses **TanStack Router** with file-based routing. The entry point is `main.tsx`:

```tsx
// main.tsx
import React from "react";
import ReactDOM from "react-dom/client";
import { RouterProvider } from "@tanstack/react-router";
import { createHashHistory, createBrowserHistory } from "@tanstack/react-router";

import "@xterm/xterm/css/xterm.css";
import "./index.css";

import { isElectron } from "./env";
import { getRouter } from "./router";
import { APP_DISPLAY_NAME } from "./branding";

const history = isElectron ? createHashHistory() : createBrowserHistory();
const router = getRouter(history);

document.title = APP_DISPLAY_NAME;

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root") as HTMLElement).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <RouterProvider router={router} />
  </React.StrictMode>,
);
```

The root layout (`__root.tsx`) provides:
- Toast providers (anchored + standard)
- Event routing for domain events and terminal events
- Error boundary with detailed error display
- Desktop project bootstrap

### 3. INDEX.HTML AND GLOBAL CSS

**index.html** (Root DOM):
- Loads DM Sans font from Google Fonts
- Mounts React app to `<div id="root">`
- Sets viewport and icons

**index.css** (Global Styling):
The file uses **Tailwind CSS 4** with advanced features:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark, .dark *));

@theme inline {
  /* Custom theme variables mapped to CSS custom properties */
  --color-warning: var(--warning);
  --color-success: var(--success);
  /* ... more theme colors ... */

  @keyframes skeleton {
    to { background-position: -200% 0; }
  }
}

@layer base {
  * { @apply border-border outline-ring/50; }
  body { @apply bg-background text-foreground relative; }
}
```

**Key Global Styles:**
- CSS custom properties for theming (see point 7)
- Transition suppression during theme changes (`.no-transitions`)
- Scrollbar customization (webkit styles)
- Markdown rendering styles (`.chat-markdown`)
- Terminal drawer styling
- Diff panel styling
- Frameless window support (drag region)
- Color scheme management in `:root`

### 4. TAILWIND CONFIGURATION

No separate `tailwind.config.js` file exists. **Tailwind v4 uses inline theme via `@theme` directive** in `index.css`. The vite.config includes `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin:

```ts
// vite.config.ts
import tailwindcss from "@tailwindcss/vite";

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [
    tanstackRouter(),
    react({ babel: { plugins: [["babel-plugin-react-compiler", { target: "19" }]] } }),
    tailwindcss(), // Tailwind v4
  ],
  // ...
});
```

### 5. PROVIDER COMPONENTS & CONTEXT

The application uses **Zustand for state management** and **TanStack Query** for server state:

**Providers in Root Layout:**
```tsx
<ToastProvider>
  <AnchoredToastProvider>
    <EventRouter />
    <DesktopProjectBootstrap />
    <Outlet />
  </AnchoredToastProvider>
</ToastProvider>
```

**Zustand Stores:**
- `useStore()` - Global app state (projects, threads, UI)
- `useComposerDraftStore()` - Composer drafts with localStorage persistence
- `useTerminalStateStore()` - Terminal states by thread/ID
- `useAppSettings()` - App settings

**Layout Provider in Chat Route:**
```tsx
