```

### 6. EXAMPLE COMPONENTS (Patterns & Styling)

**Sidebar.tsx** (100 lines shown):
- Uses shadcn UI sidebar components (`SidebarContent`, `SidebarMenu`, etc.)
- Implements thread list with status indicators
- Shows project structure with expand/collapse
- Terminal activity indicators
- Uses Tailwind classes with dynamic color classes

**ThreadTerminalDrawer.tsx** (100 lines shown):
- Uses xterm.js for terminal emulation
- Terminal theming based on light/dark mode:
  ```tsx
  function terminalThemeFromApp(): ITheme {
    const isDark = document.documentElement.classList.contains("dark");
    const bodyStyles = getComputedStyle(document.body);
    const background = bodyStyles.backgroundColor || (isDark ? "rgb(14, 18, 24)" : "rgb(255, 255, 255)");
    const foreground = bodyStyles.color || (isDark ? "rgb(237, 241, 247)" : "rgb(28, 33, 41)");

    if (isDark) {
      return { background, foreground, cursor: "rgb(180, 203, 255)", /* ... */ };
    }
    return { background, foreground, cursor: "rgb(38, 56, 78)", /* ... */ };
  }
  ```
- Dynamic drawer height management
- Terminal grid layout with split view support

**Button Component** (CVA Pattern):
Uses **class-variance-authority** for variant management:
```tsx
const buttonVariants = cva(
  "[&_svg]:-mx-0.5 relative inline-flex shrink-0 cursor-pointer...", 
  {
    variants: {
      size: { default: "h-9 px-[calc(--spacing(3)-1px)]", ... },
      variant: { 
        default: "border-primary bg-primary text-primary-foreground...",
        destructive: "border-destructive bg-destructive...",
        ghost: "border-transparent text-foreground...",
        // ...
      }
    }
  }
);
```

**Card Component** (Sophisticated Layout):
Multiple card variants with complex grid logic:
- `Card` - Basic card
- `CardFrame` - Container for multiple cards with clipping
- `CardHeader`, `CardPanel`, `CardFooter` - Sections
- Uses `data-slot` attributes for precise CSS targeting

### 7. CSS CUSTOM PROPERTIES / CSS VARIABLES

The application uses an **extensive CSS variable system** for theming:

**Theme Variables in index.css:**
```css
:root {
  color-scheme: light;
  --radius: 0.625rem;
  --background: var(--color-white);
  --foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --primary: oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --primary-foreground: var(--color-white);
  --secondary: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --muted: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --destructive: var(--color-red-500);
  --border: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 8%);
  --input: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 10%);
  --ring: oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --info: var(--color-blue-500);
  --success: var(--color-emerald-500);
  --warning: var(--color-amber-500);

  @variant dark {
    color-scheme: dark;
    --background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white));
    --foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
    /* ... dark mode overrides ... */
  }
}
```

**Variables Mapped in Tailwind Theme:**
```css
@theme inline {
  --color-primary: var(--primary);
  --color-primary-foreground: var(--primary-foreground);
  --color-background: var(--background);
  --color-foreground: var(--foreground);
  --radius-sm: calc(var(--radius) - 4px);
  --radius-md: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
  --radius-lg: var(--radius);
