# Custom Theme System — Implementation Plan

## Context

T3 Code currently has a light/dark/system appearance toggle (`useTheme()` in `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) that simply toggles a `.dark` class on `<html>`. CSS custom properties in `index.css` provide the palette for each mode. The request is to add a proper **named color theme system** — selectable palettes (t3-dark, t3-light, t3-midnight) that set CSS custom properties directly, with a UI for picking them.

The existing `useTheme()` hook's name conflicts with the new hook the requirements specify. The plan renames the existing hook to `useAppearanceMode()` and creates a new `useTheme()` for the color theme system.

---

## Files to Create

### 1. `packages/shared/src/themes.ts`

Define the `Theme` interface, three built-in themes, and the two exported functions. No dependencies — pure TypeScript, no Effect library needed.

```ts
export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface Theme {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly variant: "light" | "dark";   // controls .dark class
  readonly colors: ThemeColors;
  readonly fontFamily: string;
  readonly fontSize: number;
}

const BUILT_IN_THEMES: readonly Theme[] = [
  {
    id: "t3-dark",
    name: "T3 Dark",
    variant: "dark",
    colors: {
      background: "#0d0d12",
      foreground: "#f0f0f5",
      accent: "oklch(0.588 0.217 264)",
      sidebar: "#0a0a0f",
      editor: "#0d0d12",
      terminal: "#0a0a0f",
      statusBar: "#0a0a0f",
    },
    fontFamily: '"DM Sans", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 14,
  },
  {
    id: "t3-light",
    name: "T3 Light",
    variant: "light",
    colors: {
      background: "#ffffff",
      foreground: "#1c1c28",
      accent: "oklch(0.488 0.217 264)",
      sidebar: "#f4f4f9",
      editor: "#ffffff",
      terminal: "#f8f8fd",
      statusBar: "#f0f0f8",
    },
    fontFamily: '"DM Sans", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 14,
  },
  {
    id: "t3-midnight",
    name: "T3 Midnight",
    variant: "dark",
    colors: {
      background: "#05050a",
      foreground: "#c0c8e0",
      accent: "oklch(0.65 0.22 250)",
      sidebar: "#030308",
      editor: "#05050a",
      terminal: "#030308",
      statusBar: "#08080f",
    },
    fontFamily: '"DM Sans", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 14,
  },
];

export function getTheme(id: string): Theme {
  return BUILT_IN_THEMES.find((t) => t.id === id) ?? BUILT_IN_THEMES[0]!;
}

export function listThemes(): readonly Theme[] {
  return BUILT_IN_THEMES;
}
```

### 2. `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx`

Theme picker with swatch cards. Each card shows: a mini color preview row (4 swatches using the theme's `background`, `accent`, `sidebar`, `foreground` colors), the theme name, and a "Selected" badge.

Pattern mirrors the existing Appearance radio buttons in `_chat.settings.tsx`. No new dependencies — uses existing Tailwind classes and the `cn()` utility from `~/lib/utils`.

```tsx
import { useTheme } from "~/hooks/useTheme";
import { cn } from "~/lib/utils";

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { theme, setTheme, availableThemes } = useTheme();
  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-2 sm:grid-cols-3" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Color theme">
      {availableThemes.map((t) => {
        const selected = theme.id === t.id;
        return (
          <button key={t.id} type="button" role="radio" aria-checked={selected}
            onClick={() => setTheme(t.id)}
            className={cn(
              "flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-xl border p-3 text-left transition-colors",
              selected
                ? "border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 text-foreground"
                : "border-border bg-background text-muted-foreground hover:bg-accent",
            )}
          >
            {/* Swatch preview */}
            <div className="flex h-8 overflow-hidden rounded-md border border-border/50">
              <div className="flex-1" style={{ background: t.colors.sidebar }} />
              <div className="flex flex-[2] flex-col">
                <div className="flex-1" style={{ background: t.colors.background }} />
                <div className="h-2" style={{ background: t.colors.statusBar }} />
              </div>
              <div className="w-1" style={{ background: t.colors.accent }} />
            </div>
            <div className="flex items-center justify-between gap-2">
              <span className="text-sm font-medium">{t.name}</span>
              {selected && (
                <span className="rounded bg-primary/14 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary">
                  Active
                </span>
              )}
            </div>
          </button>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

